{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5396", "repo": "rails", "body": "I tried using regular ruby `if`/`unless`, but the only way I could get it to work wasn't very DRY:\r\n\r\n```erb\r\n<% unless @user.changed? %>\r\n  <% cache [ @user, 'form' ] do %>\r\n    ...\r\n  <% end %>\r\n<% else %>\r\n  ...\r\n<% end %>\r\n```\r\n\r\nI also tried:\r\n\r\n```erb\r\n<% unless @user.changed? %>\r\n  <% cache [ @user, 'form' ] do %>\r\n<% end %>\r\n    ...\r\n<% unless @user.changed? %>\r\n  <% end %>\r\n<% end %>\r\n```\r\n\r\nbut it didn't show anything (probably due to the `<% end %>` right after `<% cache ... %>`?).\r\n\r\nI agree it's not needed from a technical perspective, but it would be very nice to have. What do you think?", "_id": {"$oid": "523818cbbd3543c15100e0cc"}, "issue_id": 5396, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4488632", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5396#issuecomment-4488632", "updated_at": "2012-03-13T23:13:21Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sausman/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sausman/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sausman/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sausman/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/sausman", "login": "sausman", "gravatar_id": "03bcc4174eb7d5e951345f17551eac2e", "html_url": "https://github.com/sausman", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sausman/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sausman/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sausman/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/03bcc4174eb7d5e951345f17551eac2e?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fe2d8652441a60971c8af20d74e3598e7.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sausman/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 309638, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sausman/followers", "typ